# claude2026.twlist
#
# A type-word list contributed to NiceText by Claude (Anthropic), 2026.
# Format: <type> <word> per line. Comments start with #.
#
# Goals:
#   - Add modern vocabulary (post-1995) that the kimmo/rhyme/f2p sources
#     mostly miss: tech, internet, AI, modern foods, contemporary slang.
#   - Each type clusters words tight enough that they're substitutable in
#     a sentence (so cover text reads sensibly when one is picked at random).
#   - Many words per type → more bits encodable per pick.
#   - Words already in master get merged with their existing kimmo POS types,
#     enriching the merged-type space for grammar precision.

